      "tags": ["refusal", "realistic", "open-ended"],
      "_note": "Vocabulary-flexible from the model side: meaning-of-life-class queries have no canonical phrasing in the system prompt, so the model improvises in-voice (PR #26's first-run surfaced 'Not my department'). Using refusal_detected:true here would force REFUSAL_PHRASES to grow every time the model picks a new in-voice phrasing — a rubber-stamp loop that drains the literal-match assertion's signal. The voice-family contains_any tail is the honest assertion. Phase 5 Sub-task C broadens the vocabulary-flexible coverage; see ref-007..010 + docs/eval/refusal-coverage.md.",
      "assertions": [
        { "type": "rag_used", "expected": false },
        {
          "type": "source_excludes",
          "sources": ["experience", "resume", "readme", "docs"]
        },
        {
          "type": "contains_any",
          "values": ["ask me about", "not my", "not the", "wrong assistant"]
        },
        {
          "type": "not_contains",
          "values": ["42", "the meaning is", "purpose of existence"]
        }
